26/09/2010
NEW YORK, United States -- Romanian Prime Minister Emil Boc told the UN General Assembly on Friday (September 24th) that "communities all over the planet face mounting threats, which often interplay." Addressing participants in the 65th session of the assembly, Boc outlined climate change, health and population issues affecting the world's food, energy, migration and general welfare situation.
He stressed the need for multilateralism and praised the international community's growing commitment "to act collectively and share vision and willpower to overcome difficulties".
(Xinhua, Mediafax - 24/09/10)
